The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for compressed sensing MRI reconstruction, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The method also employs iterative numerical solvers, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
